JOHANNESBURG - Transport Minister Joe Maswanganyi says government is reviewing the e-toll policy.He says it's hoping to come up with a policy that is more acceptable.READ: E-tolls issue is far from resolved says MakhuraOuta estimates that the Austrian-owned collection company ETC has pocketed R2.2-billion from e-toll income since 2013.Outa chairman Wayne Duvenage said Maswangyani should realise that the scheme has completely failed."He should make decisions and move to sucessful road-funding mechanisms like the fuel levy," said Duvenhage.eNCA